Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and slice @Zucchini{1} crosswise into ½-inch-thick rounds. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and halve @Lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and @Parmesan Cheese{3%tablespoon} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Cut @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. (Save zucchini for another use.)

Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}, half the Tuscan Heat Spice (you'll use the rest in the next step), salt, and pepper.

Arrange zucchini in a single layer so they are touching but not overlapping. Top with panko mixture.

Roast on top rack until zucchini is tender and panko is golden brown and crispy, ~{15-18%minutes}.

> Swap in broccoli for zucchini; roast until browned and tender, 15-20 minutes.

Meanwhile, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with remaining @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While chicken cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Israeli Couscous{2.5%ounce}; stir until toasted, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), half the @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2%unit} (you'll use the rest in the next step), and a pinch of salt. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Heat pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add remaining stock concentrates, ¼ cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings), and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Simmer until slightly reduced, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon} and @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted and combined. Season with salt and pepper.

To pot with couscous, add juice from half the lemon, half the lemon zest, half the scallion greens, salt, and pepper; stir to combine.

> If couscous seems dry, add a splash of water. For extra richness, stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Divide couscous, chicken, and zucchini between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken. Top with remaining scallion greens and lemon zest. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.